column5: Hey all, leave for Lac Seul in the am, any recent reports? Thx!
Ya might wanna say whereabouts on Lac Seul….Silver Water Wheel Lodge does a weekly ‘report’ which is sometimes helpfulhttps://www.sww-lodge.com/category/fishing-report/
Yep I follow that also, I fish mostly the Northwest part of Lac Seul primarily. Thx

Leaving for Onaway in the morning, too. Safe travels. Always a great time up there! Sounds like water levels are "normal". After a year of near record lows (2021) followed by near record highs (last year) I'm happy about that.
Leaving Friday morning to head up. I’ll be on the SE side.

DEEP .as in best bite is barotrauma times. Shallow bite was ok. That early 4 weeks of heat in June really changed the game for this time of yr. It's gonna cool down per forecast hopefully they move back to 18-22ft otherwise best bite is 30-35. Most people's fish I seen in fish cleaning the past 8 days were eyes bulging on almost everything. I chose not to partake in that. So yes we caught less. But I'm not that guy, and I doubt most realized what they were doin
